Class Vertex

java.lang.Object
  SimObject
      Vertex
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Vertex>
public class Vertex
extends SimObject
implements Comparable<Vertex>

This class holds the information for each Vertex in the graph for the WumpusHunt game. These Vertexes can be one of 5 types.

Type 0 : this Vertex is an "opening" in the cave system and is a place that the Hunter and/or Wumpus can sit

Type 1: North and East neighbors are connected via a path. As well as West and South neighbors

Type 2: North and West neighbors are connected via a path. As well as East and South neighbors

Type 3: North and South neighbors connected via a path only

Type 4: East and West neighbors connected via a path only

private Map<Vertex.Direction,Vertex> map

Method Detail

creatUniqueLabel

private String creatUniqueLabel()
This private method will create the unique string for the newly initialized Vertex. This is based off of the totalNum static variable. The label will assign the Vertex to a character between a-z and then after every multiple of 26 Vertexes are created it will expand the label to include another character of the same letter.

For example: the first vertex is 'a' and the 27the Vertex is 'aa' and so on.

This labeling can be bad for large cave systems as it does not take full advantage of the number of labels it can assign with each character

Returns:
Unique label for the Vertex
